race.comment: Great race this. OPPORTUNISTIC (1) flew home first-up over this track and trip when favourite, missing by 1.5L but clocking splits good enough to say he's picked up where he left off. CJP rides now from a better barrier and while staying at 1400m is a query, he does have plenty of class. SEPTEMBER BORN (6) returns to the races for the first time in nearly a year but has been sighted at the trials across two separate campaigns. Only 1 trial coming into this, but it was solid enough and the inside draw suggests he can be close to the speed first-up. Plenty of hype around him and he should get his chance to deliver. ROYAL TORONADO (7) has impressed at the trials coming into this and looks destined to get over further this time in work. Pike riding is a good push for his chances and if he's sharp enough, he'll be right in the finish. DEEL HER IN (10) looks an improver out to 1400m now and is not to be discounted. ASPHALT (9) has to raise the bar again but he's doing so with ease recently.
